Commentary Text: Washington Sundar to Chris Lynn, out Caught&Bowled!! Another master move by Kohli! He's been smart with his bowling changes and there's no set pattern for the opponents to expect. Washi gets turns from his home pitch and Lynn miscued the slog completely. looked like it hit him on the outside half and sligjtly high too. Washi knew there was no mid-on or mid-wicket. so raced back from his bowling crease, judged it really well and took it over his shoulders. A good debut for Lynn. Had to dig deep after running the captain out. Chris Lynn c and b Washington Sundar 49(35) [4s-4 6s-3]

Commentary Text: Chahal to Chris Lynn, out Rohit Run Out!! A mix-up out there, and Rohit's gone! Oh dear. He was really keen for the single, but from halfway down Lynn sends him back. It's too late. Slightly short ball just outside off, Lynn mistimes the cut in between two fielders at cover and cover-point. He takes a couple of steps initially, which really sets Rohit off. But then Lynn backs out. And with Kohli swooping onto the ball, there's no getting back. Massive blow. Will it weigh on Lynn now? Rohit run out (Kohli/Chahal) 19(15) [4s-1 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Marco Jansen to de Villiers, out de Villiers Run Out!! 1 run completed. Madness. Absolute madness. AB - in his greed to keep his strike - quite deliberately nurdles this very softly through mid-wicket, and despite Krunal Pandya getting to the ball by the time he was turning around for the second, he doesn't stop.
